The White House has announced that the 2014 White House Easter Egg Roll will take place on Monday, April 21st. The event aims to open the People's House to as many people as possible and support the First Lady's Let's Move! initiative. It will feature sports courts, cooking stations, Easter egg rolling, live music, and storytelling. Tickets will be distributed through an online lottery system, and the lottery will open on March 7th and close on March 10th. The tickets are free and non-transferable. More information can be found on the official White House website. Media details will be released at a later date.